<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="516" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1503,1709]" pageId="11" pageNumber="516">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1612,1637]" pageId="11" pageNumber="516">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was described from the two above mentioned specimens. Zerny compared it to 
<taxonomicName authority="Dyar, 1910" authorityName="Dyar" authorityYear="1910" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Episcepsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="516" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="frances">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="516">E. frances</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Dyar" box="[241,369,1648,1672]" pageId="11" pageNumber="516" refString="Dyar, H. G. (1910) Descriptions of some new species and genera of Lepidoptera from Mexico. Proceedings of the United States National Museum, 38, 229 - 273. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00963801.38 - 1742.229" type="journal article" year="1910">
Dyar, 
<number box="[310,369,1648,1672]" pageId="11" pageNumber="516" value="1910.0">1910</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Dyar" box="[381,393,1648,1671]" pageId="11" pageNumber="516" refString="Dyar, H. G. (1910) Descriptions of some new species and genera of Lepidoptera from Mexico. Proceedings of the United States National Museum, 38, 229 - 273. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00963801.38 - 1742.229" type="journal article" year="1910" yearSuffix="a">a</bibRefCitation>
species from 
<collectingCountry box="[551,639,1647,1672]" name="Mexico" pageId="11" pageNumber="516">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, which is indeed remarkably similar. Both species are close in habitus, and share the peculiar hindwing androconia found in the 
<typeStatus box="[789,837,1685,1709]" pageId="11" pageNumber="516">type</typeStatus>
species of the genus, 
<taxonomicName box="[1083,1189,1685,1708]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Episcepsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="516" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="venata">
<emphasis box="[1083,1189,1685,1708]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="516">E. venata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
